I get it's not a bad card, but I don't see it as a great one either.
Henry needs more Golgari in his heart(s)
The land's ability is pretty expensive. I mean paying 6 to return a creature to the battlefield isn't amazing. It's fine.
Yeah. I dont expect it to be amazing. But recursion that doesnt cost me card advantage should be expensive

It does a lot of thing. It’s probably the easiest of the DFCs to flip as it only requires a creature to die. You get said creature back (with whatever ETB/ value it has), and then get a repeatable instant speed reanimate on a rainbow land.
heads
I mean, recursion to the field by definition doesn't cost you a card :wink:

Most reanimate effects nowadays are four mana, which is the more balanced rate. Two mana extra and you can do it every turn. Amazing? Eh, but it’s very good, and I think it sees play over a lot of other cards.

I think Journey has a lot more overlap than other cards in RIX.
Sure...again, it's a fine card, just wasn't sure about the love it seems to get to be in the top 5 of many folk's lists.

Yeah. The front side isn't flashy, but given that most creatures in reanimator style decks have potent ETBs, being able to reuse one isn't terrible. 

From there it's fixing, and grinds for advantage if the game slows down. 

For me it's top 3 because it's more ubiquitous than a lot of other cards. Most GB reanimation decks should consider it.

For me, it’s because more decks can use it. There’s a lot of GB decks that have creatures die and can get value from reanimating them.

A lot of other good cards from RIX need more specific homes, even if the ceiling may be higher in those decks.
One must risk it, for the biscuit.
